FBIS3-49014 "dreeu002_h_94007" FBIS-EEU-94-002 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Jan 1994 HUNGARY National Bank Devalues Forint by 1 Percent LD0101165194 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 1600 GMT 1 Jan 94 LD0101165194 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network Language: Hungarian Article Type:BFN [Text] The forint will be devalued by 1 percent as of 3 January. The decision was made by the Hungarian National Bank [MNB] within its scope of authority. The MNB gave the strengthening of the U.S. dollar on international foreign exchange markets as the reason for the decision. A communique points out that the measure is in line with the MNB's official exchange rate policy.
